    <thetext>This example gives a wrong warning:

// ---
import org.eclipse.jdt.annotation.*;

interface NNFunc {
	@NonNull String a(@NonNull String i);
}
public class PolyNull {
	@NonNull String extract1(NNFunc f, @NonNull String s) { return f.a(s); }
	@NonNull String test1() {
		return extract1(i -&gt; i, &quot;hallo&quot;); // bogus warning
	}
}
// ---

Warning is:
Null type safety (type annotations): The expression of type &apos;@NonNull String&apos; needs unchecked conversion to conform to &apos;@NonNull String&apos;

The warning is wrong because the lambda argument &apos;i&apos; is actually @NonNull.</thetext>
